[Posted and mailed]
In article <368ABCC3.32527EB5@shiresoft.com>,
        "Guy G. Sotomayor" <ggs@shiresoft.com> writes:
> Can someone tell me how to get knfsd to work on 2.1.131?  I guess I'm
> missing something obvious -- I can't get it to work.  I'm also using the
> knfsd-981204 utilities that go along with it.
> 
> I want to try this out, because my sparc solaris systems keep getting
> "NFS server not responding keep trying" messages when ever I try to use
> a file system mounted from Linux.  My other Linux boxes don't have any
> problems talking to the Linux NFS server.
This is a very old and very well known problem.  Knfsd does not work
when it tries "NFS over TCP".  Until this feature is fixed or disabled,
you need to specify "-proto=udp" in vfstab (or auto_home, whatever) on
your Solaris boxes.
Eugene
